# Hookbase webhook handler — Next.js + {{PROVIDER_LABEL}}

```bash
npm install
cp .env.example .env.local
npm run dev
```

POSTs land at `http://localhost:3000/webhook`. The route handler is at `app/webhook/route.ts`.

Use `hookbase listen 3000` to expose your local dev server through a Hookbase tunnel, then point your destination at `<tunnel-url>/webhook`.
